interpretation: The "eject button" card represents a need to let go of something or someone that no longer serves a purpose in your life. It may be time to break free from a toxic relationship, a dead-end job, or a bad habit. This card reminds you that you have the power to take control of your life and make positive changes. It may be a difficult decision, but ultimately it will lead to a sense of liberation and freedom. Keywords associated with this card include release, detachment, and closure. Trust in yourself and know that you are capable of making the right choice for your own well-being. The "eject button" card may also indicate a need for self-reflection and introspection in order to determine what is holding you back and what needs to be released.
